<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Bir Bölüm Üç Açı - İşletme Mezun &amp; Öğrenci" width="720" height="405" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/r2IZK4-joDM?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
</div></figure>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Ozyegin University&#8217;s Faculty of Business Administration offers a modern educational experience at Istanbul&#8217;s Çekmeköy Campus. Its LEED-certified sustainable building supports both academic and social development of students with its large classrooms, student offices and social areas.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Departments in the Faculty of Business Administration:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Business</li>



<li>International Finance</li>



<li>Economy</li>



<li>International Trade and Business Management</li>



<li>Management Information Systems</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">This wide range of departments gives students the chance to specialize in different fields and shape their careers in the business world. For more information and campus details, please visit <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/ozyegin-kampus-konum/">Özyeğin University Campus and Location Guide</a>.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="education-fees-and-scholarship-opportunities-2025-2026-year">Education Fees and Scholarship Opportunities 2025-2026 Year</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The annual tuition fee for the Faculty of Business Administration at Ozyegin University is set at $22,000 for the 2025-2026 academic year. Students can earn significant discounts on this fee thanks to merit scholarships. Here are sample scholarship plans:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Scholarship Rate</th>
<th>Discounted Fee</th>
<th>Prepayment</th>
<th>1st Installment (Fall)</th>
<th>2. Installment (Spring)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>50%</td>
<td>$11,000</td>
<td>$1,000</td>
<td>$4,500</td>
<td>$5,500</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>
<blockquote class="wp-block-quote">


<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Note:</strong> All applicants are considered for the scholarship, no separate application is required. Scholarship rates are determined based on criteria such as diploma grade, national and international exam results, certificates, motivation letters and letters of reference.</p>


</blockquote>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Health insurance, technology fees, food and dormitory fees are not included in the annual tuition fee. There may also be additional fees specific to programs such as piloting, culinary arts and hotel management.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For more information, please visit Özyeğin University <a href="https://admissions.ozyegin.edu.tr/tr/ucretler-ve-burslar" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Fees and Scholarships</a> page.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="bachelor-of-business-administration-program-general-structure-and-course-content">Bachelor of Business Administration Program: General Structure and Course Content</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Ozyeğin University&#8217;s Business Administration Undergraduate Program offers a balanced academic structure to help students make a strong entry into the business world.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="basic-courses-and-the-first-two-years">Basic Courses and the First Two Years</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>During the first two years, students build a strong foundation by taking core business courses and required program courses.</li>



<li>The program offers an infrastructure that prepares students for the business world in areas such as business management, marketing, finance and economics.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="elective-courses-and-sector-experience">Elective Courses and Sector Experience</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>In the third and fourth years, students have the chance to specialize in their areas of interest through elective courses.</li>



<li>Optional courses include Marketing, Finance, Operations Management, Management and Management Information Systems.</li>



<li>They can further personalize their education by taking elective courses outside the faculty (e.g. social entrepreneurship, foreign languages).</li>



<li>The program aims to enable students to produce solutions to real problems they will encounter in the business world with courses that reinforce theoretical knowledge with applied projects.</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="specialized-areas-in-business-shape-your-career">Specialized Areas in Business: Shape Your Career</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Faculty of Business Administration allows students to graduate by specializing in a specific field.</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Specialized Areas</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Marketing</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Finance</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Operations Management</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Management</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Management Information Systems</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</tbody>
</table>
</table>
</figure>
<blockquote class="wp-block-quote">


<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Note:</strong> Students with 90 ECTS credits and above can choose their specialization areas by taking four in-program/field elective courses (24 ECTS in total). It is not compulsory to choose a specialization; students who wish to continue as &#8220;General Business Administration&#8221; can do so.</p>


</blockquote>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">This flexible structure offers students a program that can be tailored to their interests and career goals.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="graduation-requirements-the-road-to-success">Graduation Requirements: The Road to Success</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In order to graduate from the Business Administration Undergraduate Program, students must complete the following requirements:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Type of Course</th>
<th>Number of Courses</th>
<th>Total Credits</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Compulsory Courses</td>
<td>32</td>
<td>164</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Program-Intra/Field Elective Courses</td>
<td>4</td>
<td>24</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>In-Faculty Elective Courses</td>
<td>4</td>
<td>24</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Out-of-Faculty Elective Courses</td>
<td>2</td>
<td>12</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Free Elective Courses</td>
<td>2</td>
<td>12</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<tr>
<td>Compulsory Internship/Certificate</td>
<td>&#8211;</td>
<td>4</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Total</strong></td>
<td><strong>44</strong></td>
<td><strong>240 ECTS</strong></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Students must also successfully complete a compulsory internship program of at least eight weeks. Specialization areas are also indicated in the diploma supplements, contributing to the graduates&#8217; prominence in the business world.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="sectoral-solutions-courses-combine-theory-and-practice">Sectoral Solutions Courses: Combine Theory and Practice</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Sectoral Solutions courses provide a great opportunity for students to get ready for the world of work.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Experience in Real Projects</strong>: Students gain experience by doing projects with real companies in different sectors such as finance, healthcare, FMCG, etc.</li>



<li><strong>Stepping into the Business World</strong>: Thanks to the compulsory internship program and practical courses, students take a solid step into the business world.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These courses provide students with both knowledge and practical experience, preparing them for the world of work after graduation.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-faculty-of-business-at-ozyegin-university-is-waiting-for-you">The Faculty of Business at Ozyegin University is Waiting for You</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">As you can see, Ozyegin University&#8217;s Faculty of Business Administration offers students an education that provides not only academic but also sectoral experience with its modern campus, wide range of department options and scholarship opportunities. To make a difference in the business world, you can get detailed information on <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Road to Study</a> and apply now!</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2025-07-23T11:20:03Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T18:47:20Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/ozyegin-university-faculty-of-business-administration.webp","alt":"Özyeğin University Faculty of Business Administration modern campus building and classrooms","title":"ozyegin-university-faculty-of-business-administration"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'ozyegin-university-faculty-of-business-administration' );
