<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="young-and-experienced-academic-staff">Young and Experienced Academic Staff</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The faculty&#8217;s strong academic staff includes:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>5 Professor</li>



<li>2 Associate Professor</li>



<li>22 Dr. Faculty Member</li>



<li>3 Lecturer</li>



<li>20 Research Assistants<br>. This team consists of people with both national and international expertise. In addition, guest lecturers from different universities also provide information diversity by giving lectures.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="modern-campus-facilities-and-law-clinics">Modern Campus Facilities and Law Clinics</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Çekmeköy Campus is equipped with modern classrooms, digital libraries and social areas. Faculty of Law:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Courtroom designed according to the Continental European Legal System</li>



<li>Courtroom designed according to the Anglo-Saxon legal system</li>



<li>Law clinics and practice laboratories<br>are available. Thanks to these opportunities, students gain experience in a real case environment before they graduate.</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="rich-curriculum-and-interdisciplinary-laboratories">Rich Curriculum and Interdisciplinary Laboratories</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The curriculum of Ozyegin University Faculty of Law is supported by theoretical courses, applied clinical studies and interdisciplinary laboratories. Considering that law is not a one-dimensional education, this faculty aims to educate its students as individuals equipped in different fields.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="certificate-courses-and-practical-law-training">Certificate Courses and Practical Law Training</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Thanks to the certificate courses offered at the faculty, students can:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Penal Law</li>



<li>Maritime and Transportation Law</li>



<li>Company Law Practices</li>



<li>Practices of Intellectual Property Law</li>



<li>Applications of Administrative Law</li>



<li>Constitutional Theory and Practice</li>



<li>Information Law</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">By specializing in their fields, they gain an advantage after graduation. At least one certificate course must be successfully passed for graduation.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="elective-courses-and-specialization-areas">Elective Courses and Specialization Areas</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Students can personalize their legal education with elective courses within and outside the faculty. In addition to compulsory courses, innovative courses such as Social Responsibility and Law, Project Cycle are also included in the program. While the language of instruction is Turkish, students can also take elective courses in a foreign language when they reach a certain language level. In this way, students graduate with the knowledge and skills to compete not only in Turkey but also on international platforms.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="courtrooms-and-fictional-trial-experience">Courtrooms and Fictional Trial Experience</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When studying at a law school, it is very important to experience practical applications in addition to theoretical knowledge. Özyeğin University Faculty of Law stands out in this regard. Two different courtrooms on the campus are designed according to both Continental European and Anglo-Saxon legal systems.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="continental-europe-and-anglo-saxon-legal-systems">Continental Europe and Anglo-Saxon Legal Systems</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Thanks to these two courtrooms, students gain experience by observing the functioning of different legal systems. In this way, they acquire a flexible legal knowledge that can work both in Turkey and on international platforms. In addition, students working in interdisciplinary laboratories gain awareness in innovative areas such as the law of violence, children&#8217;s rights and artificial intelligence law.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="moot-court-virtual-court-applications">Moot Court: Virtual Court Applications</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Moot Court is one of the most exciting activities for students. In these activities, which are similar to real cases, students carry out a case process from start to finish under the supervision of academic staff. This experience enables students to develop multidimensional thinking, analysis and interpretation skills. These experiences, close to the real court environment, greatly facilitate students&#8217; preparation for professional life after graduation.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="graduation-and-career-opportunities">Graduation and Career Opportunities</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The career opportunities offered to graduates of Ozyegin University Faculty of Law are also quite remarkable. For graduation, students must complete at least 240 ECTS and have a graduation average of at least 2.00. In addition, students are required to complete a compulsory internship of at least 40 working days. These internships enable students to put their theoretical knowledge into practice and gain experience in a real legal environment.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="internship-opportunities-and-sectoral-collaborations">Internship Opportunities and Sectoral Collaborations</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Internship opportunities at leading law firms in Turkey and abroad</li>



<li>Internship evaluation process based on grade point average and language proficiency</li>



<li>Significant advantage in finding a job after graduation</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="law-career-paths-after-graduation">Law Career Paths After Graduation</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Students who graduate from law school can pursue careers as lawyers, judges and prosecutors, as well as legal consultants in companies or specializing in various fields. Özyeğin University&#8217;s hands-on education and interdisciplinary approach ensures that its graduates are prepared for a competitive legal career both in Turkey and internationally.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="take-your-first-step-for-legal-education">Take Your First Step for Legal Education!</h2>


<p>All you need to do now to study at Özyeğin University Law School is to take the first step! You can take a look at the <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">RoadtoStudy application guide</a></p>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">and get detailed information. Get both theoretical and practical education with law school experience and become one of the successful lawyers of the future!</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2025-07-23T11:01:09Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T18:47:21Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/ozyegin-university-faculty-of-law.webp","alt":"Özyeğin University Faculty of Law campus building","title":"ozyegin-university-faculty-of-law"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'ozyegin-university-faculty-of-law' );
