<th>Annual Tuition (Approximate)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Full Scholarship</td>
<td>0 USD</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>50% Scholarship</td>
<td>11.000 USD</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Paid</td>
<td>22,000 USD</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Scholarship applications can be made during the application process and during the academic year. If you have a good GPA, you have the chance to win additional scholarships. This both motivates students and makes costs more affordable.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="sample-payment-plan-50-scholarship">Sample Payment Plan (50% Scholarship)</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">🎓 <strong>Discounted Tuition:</strong> $11,000<br>✅ <strong>Prepayment:</strong> $1,000<br>📌 <strong>1st Installment (Fall Semester):</strong> $5,000 (less prepayment)<br>📌 <strong>2nd Installment (Spring Semester):</strong> $6,000</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Scholarship evaluations take into account diploma grades, national and international exam results, certificates, motivation letters and reference letters. Your scholarship rate is indicated in the acceptance e-mail and no separate e-mail is sent.</p>


<blockquote class="wp-block-quote">


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Note: Health insurance, technology fees, food and dormitory fees are not included in the annual tuition fee. Additional fees may apply in programs such as Pilotage, Gastronomy and Hotel Management.</p>


</blockquote>
