<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="career-opportunities-and-alumni-success-stories">Career Opportunities and Alumni Success Stories</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The economics sector opens a wide range of doors for graduates of Ozyegin University Department of Economics. The internship requirement and project-based courses at the core of the program enable students to meet the business world before graduation. Graduates can find career opportunities in many fields such as banking, financial consulting, economic analysis and strategic planning in international companies.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="career-fields-after-graduation">Career Fields After Graduation:</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Banking and Financial Consulting</li>



<li>Economic Analysis and Strategic Planning in International Companies</li>



<li>Economic Research Organizations and Think-Tanks</li>



<li>Public Sector (such as Central Bank, Undersecretariat of Treasury)</li>



<li>Entrepreneurship and Start-up Ecosystem</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-requirements-and-admission-process">Application Requirements and Admission Process</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Higher Education Institutions Exam (YKS) EA score is required to apply to the department. During the application process to <strong>Özyeğin University Department of Economics</strong>, scores, English proficiency exams and required documents are uploaded to the system to complete the application process. For international students, it is supported by documents such as diplomas and transcripts.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="steps-of-the-application-process">Steps of the Application Process:</h3>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li>Application with YKS or equivalent international exam results</li>



<li>English Proficiency (TOEFL/IELTS or OzU English exam)</li>



<li>Filling out the online application form</li>



<li>Upload required documents</li>



<li>Post-admission registration and English preparatory exemption exam</li>
</ol>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Program Type</th>
<th>2025-2026 Base Point (EA)</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Full Scholarship</td>
<td>506,87% (~814)</td>
<td>Preparatory + 4 years scholarship</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>50% Discount</td>
<td>347.4 (~170k)</td>
<td>50% discount on tuition</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Fee</td>
<td>300k+ (Queue)</td>
<td>Approximately 22.000 USD/year</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Passing the English proficiency exam and skipping the preparation saves students time. Especially students with good English skills can gain an advantage by starting the department directly.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For more detailed information, you can check the university&#8217;s <a href="https://www.ozyegin.edu.tr/tr" target="_blank" rel="noopener">official application page</a>.</p>


