udy in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/what-are-apostille-procedures-in-turkey.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/what-are-apostille-procedures-in-turkey.webp","width":"1168","height":"880","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/what-are-apostille-procedures-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/what-are-apostille-procedures-in-turkey/","name":"What are Apostille Procedures in Turkey? How is it done?","datePublished":"2025-12-11T15:58:30+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:48:50+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/what-are-apostille-procedures-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"What are Apostille Procedures in Turkey? How is it done?","keywords":"Apostille Procedures","datePublished":"2025-12-11T15:58:30+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:48:50+03:00","articleSection":"Visa and Immigration","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Apostille is an official approval system that allows a document to be legally used in another country by certifying its authenticity and the accuracy of its","name":"What are Apostille Procedures in Turkey? How is it done?","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/what-are-apostille-procedures-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/what-are-apostille-procedures-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/what-are-apostille-procedures-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/what-are-apostille-procedures-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-is-apostille-apostille-procedures-in-turkey">What is Apostille? Apostille Procedures in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Apostille is an official approval system that allows a document to be legally used in another country by certifying its authenticity and the accuracy of its content. Established by the October 6, 1961 Hague Convention, this system is only valid between party or member countries. In Turkey, apostille procedures are quite common especially for student documents and provide great convenience in areas such as university applications and visa procedures. Details of the Convention are available on the <a href="https://www.hcch.net/en/home" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hague Conference official website</a>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="where-to-obtain-apostille-in-turkey">Where to Obtain Apostille in Turkey</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Apostille procedures in Turkey are carried out at District Governorships and Governorships. Consulates usually approve documents for Turkish citizens abroad; however, local District Governorships are authorized for apostille procedures within Turkey. Especially for student documents, it is usually necessary to apply to the district governorship or provincial governorship of the district of residence. Apostille procedures in Turkey are quite fast and can usually be completed within the same day.</p>


