<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 23px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="apostille-procedures-at-the-consulate-and-district-governorship">Apostille Procedures at the Consulate and District Governorship</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The most frequently asked question for those who want to have their student documents apostilled in Turkey is how the process will be carried out in which institution. The consulate and the district governorship play different roles in this process.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="consulate-apostille-procedures-and-required-documents">Consulate Apostille Procedures and Required Documents</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are a student in a country other than Turkey or if you want to obtain an apostille abroad, you can apply to the relevant consulate in Turkey. Consulates usually perform apostille or attestation procedures for official documents in that country to be used in Turkey. Passport, copy of ID and the original document are required at the time of application. <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-pasaport-ve-evrak-guvenligi/" data-type="post" data-id="9827">Consulate</a> procedures can take some time, so it is better to apply early.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="kaymakamlik-apostille-fees-and-process">Kaymakamlik Apostille Fees and Process</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The most common place for student documents in Turkey is the District Governorship or Governor&#8217;s Office. The original and a photocopy of the document, as well as a photocopy of the identity card, are submitted for apostille. As of 2025, there is no fixed fee for apostille procedures at District Governorships, i.e. the procedures are free of charge. However, some documents (e.g. <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-vize-ikamet-tercume-ve-noter/" data-type="post" data-id="3868">documents requiring notarization</a>) may require prior notarization, which may mean an additional fee. After the documents are examined, an apostille annotation is added and the process is completed. Apostille is usually delivered on the same day.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Ministry of Foreign Affairs Revenue Administration announced that the certification fee for the year 2025 is <strong>approximately 19.31 USD</strong> per document. The fee is charged separately per document and is usually collected against a receipt or a receipt. The latest announcements on the subject can be found on the Ministry of Foreign Affairs&#8217; <a>official website</a>.</p>


