<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Although the Apostille process may seem simple, if you do not pay attention to some critical points, you may lose time and your application may be rejected. Here are the most common mistakes and solutions:</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequent-mistakes-and-solution-suggestions">Frequent Mistakes and Solution Suggestions</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Many students or parents submit photocopies or digital printouts of their documents to the district governor&#8217;s office. However, the original document must be presented for the apostille process. In addition, forgetting a photocopy of your ID or bringing the wrong document also prolongs the process. Make sure your documents are complete and accurate before submitting them.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="tips-for-apostille-and-attestation">Tips for Apostille and Attestation</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Before submitting your document to the District Governorate or Governorate, check that it is dated, signed and stamped. For incomplete or unsigned documents, you may need to get approval from the relevant authority first. Also, don&#8217;t forget to take documents that require notarization to a notary first and have them notarized.</p>


