<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="is-notarization-required-for-an-apostille">Is notarization required for an apostille?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Apostille is applied to the <strong>original</strong> or <strong>a duly certified copy</strong> of a document. Which documents can be directly apostilled is determined by the Governor&#8217;s Office or the Presidency of the Justice Commission; generally, official documents do not require <strong>additional notarization</strong>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="can-you-get-an-apostille-from-e-government">Can you get an apostille from e-government?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>E-Devlet</strong> can be used to <strong>verify</strong> certain documents (e.g., criminal records, student certificates), but <strong>physical apostille certification</strong> (signature and seal) requires <strong>in person</strong> or <strong>by proxy</strong> to authorized institutions.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2025-12-11T12:58:30Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T18:48:50Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/what-are-apostille-procedures-in-turkey.webp","alt":"What are Apostille Procedures in Turkey? How is it done?","title":"what-are-apostille-procedures-in-turkey"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'what-are-apostille-procedures-in-turkey' );
