<iframe loading="lazy" title="Bir Bölüm Üç Açı - Uluslararası Ticaret ve İşletmecilik Mezun &amp; Öğrenci" width="720" height="405" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/zUhaVKQco5M?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
</div></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="why-ozyegin-university">Why Ozyegin University?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The global economy is more intertwined than ever. You need to know how to do business not only in your own country, but also in markets around the world. This is where the <strong>International Trade and Business Administration</strong> department comes in. This program provides students with a solid business foundation as well as the ability to work with different cultures, make strategic decisions and compete in global markets. If you dream of a career in multinational companies or taking your own business international, this field may be ideal for you.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="english-education-and-modern-campus-facilities">English Education and Modern Campus Facilities</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The International Trade and Business Administration Program is entirely in English. This is a great advantage, especially for students who want to work in multinational companies or pursue a master&#8217;s degree abroad. The campus is located in a lush green area in Çekmeköy, in the east of Istanbul. The library is open 24 hours a day, the gyms, dormitories and café areas are very modern.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="living-in-istanbul-city-life-and-cultural-richness">Living in Istanbul: City Life and Cultural Richness</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Studying in Istanbul is sometimes chaotic but mostly exciting. Although Özyeğin University is located in a quiet neighborhood, it is easily accessible to the city center. This offers students both a peaceful campus life and a dynamic city experience. Museums, concerts, walking on the Bosphorus&#8230; All here, one tram away.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="special-support-offices-for-international-students">Special Support Offices for International Students</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The university has an active International Office. They help students with visa extensions, internship documents, health insurance, etc.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><em>For more information, check out the university&#8217;s <a href="https://admissions.ozyegin.edu.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">official website</a>.</em></p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="2025-2026-education-fees-and-scholarship-options">2025-2026 Education Fees and Scholarship Options</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Studying at a private university in Turkey is usually expensive, but Özyeğin University&#8217;s scholarship opportunities allow many international students to access this program. So even if your budget is not very high, if you have a good academic background, this opportunity may still be possible for you.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="fee-50-scholarship-and-full-scholarship-options">Fee, 50% Scholarship and Full Scholarship Options</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The tuition fee for the 2025-2026 academic year is approximately as follows:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Full Scholarship</strong>: $0 (i.e. completely free)</li>



<li><strong>50% Scholarship</strong>: $11,000</li>



<li><strong>Paid (without scholarship)</strong>: $22,000</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are many students studying with scholarships, and these scholarships are automatically evaluated during the application process. Scholarships based on academic achievement are valid for four years.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-the-payment-plan-works">How the Payment Plan Works</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For example, the payment of a student with a 50% scholarship can be planned as follows:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Payment in advance: $1,000</li>



<li>Installment for Fall Semester: $5,000</li>



<li>Spring Semester Installment: $5,000</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">To be honest, this plan gave me a lot of comfort when I was discussing the budget with my family. Thanks to the possibility of payment in installments, it is possible to spread the costs.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="success-based-additional-scholarships-and-conditions">Success Based Additional Scholarships and Conditions</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If your GPA is above a certain level (usually 3.30 and above), you have the chance to get additional scholarships. These scholarships are a great support not only financially but also in terms of motivation. Students who keep their grades high can continue school with additional support from the second grade onwards.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="academic-program-becoming-an-international-trade-expert-in-4-years">Academic Program: Becoming an International Trade Expert in 4 Years</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">This department is not just a place to say &#8220;we are studying business administration&#8221;. The program is structured in such a way that you gain different skills each year. After 4 years, you become someone who knows what to say when you sit at the table in a multinational company.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="1st-year-introduction-to-business-ethics-economics-and-entrepreneurship">1st Year: Introduction to Business Ethics, Economics and Entrepreneurship</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In the first year, you are introduced to the world of business with the basics of economics. It is even possible to develop your own business idea in entrepreneurship courses.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="2nd-year-intercultural-communication-and-basic-business-infrastructure">2nd Year: Intercultural Communication and Basic Business Infrastructure</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Basic business courses such as marketing, finance and operations management come into play here. Especially the &#8220;intercultural communication&#8221; course teaches you how to work with people from different countries, not just how to give presentations.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="3rd-year-trade-and-business-from-an-international-perspective">3rd Year: Trade and Business from an International Perspective</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">As of this year, the focus of the program is all about internationalization. Courses like &#8220;Global Supply Chain&#8221; help you understand how companies make decisions on a global scale. You can also look at different fields by taking elective courses from other departments within the faculty.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="4th-year-specialization-and-real-world-applications">4th Year: Specialization and Real World Applications</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In the last year, the focus has been on topics such as creating a global strategy and doing business in specific geographies. You take part in projects that overlap with real life and work with academics who are experts in their fields. When you graduate, you feel not only &#8220;diploma&#8221; but &#8220;ready.&#8221;</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-do-graduates-of-international-trade-and-business-administration-do">What Do Graduates of International Trade and Business Administration Do?</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="job-opportunities-in-multinational-companies">Job Opportunities in Multinational Companies</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Particularly FMCG (fast-moving consumer goods), logistics, finance and technology companies prefer this department. Graduates usually start with positions such as &#8220;business analyst&#8221;, &#8220;project manager&#8221; or &#8220;regional marketing specialist&#8221;. Companies such as Deloitte, Unilever, Amazon are closely following potential graduates in this field.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="entrepreneurship-and-self-employment">Entrepreneurship and Self-Employment</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you have a dream of starting your own business, this department will give you the foundations. Özyeğin&#8217;s entrepreneurship ecosystem is very active. There are incubation centers, mentoring programs and opportunities to connect with investors.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="academic-and-masters-degree-alternatives">Academic and Master&#8217;s Degree Alternatives</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you have the idea of pursuing a master&#8217;s degree abroad after graduation in fields such as MBA or international relations, this program is also suitable for that. Since the medium of instruction is English, you don&#8217;t need much additional preparation other than TOEFL or IELTS.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="zorunlu-internship-and-study-abroad-opportunities">Compulsory Internship and Study Abroad Opportunities</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Theoretical education is important, but real experience is essential if you want to make a difference in the business world. One of the most beautiful features of this department is that it offers you this experience before you graduate.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="two-phase-internship-system">Two Phase Internship System</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Students are required to complete two short-term internships before graduation. These internships are usually held during the summer months and take place in highly qualified companies thanks to the school&#8217;s <strong>Sectoral Solutions Program</strong>.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="erasmus-and-exchange-programs">Erasmus and Exchange Programs</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Erasmus and bilateral exchange programs are also available for students who want to study abroad. Thanks to these programs, you can get the chance to study in Europe for 1 or 2 semesters. Some students combine this period with an internship and use it as an &#8220;international internship&#8221; experience.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="internship-abroad-with-international-office-support">Internship Abroad with International Office Support</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The International Office is a great help for students who want to do an internship abroad. The seemingly complex steps such as application documents, visa process, company correspondence become very manageable thanks to the guidance of the office.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="international-trade-and-business-first-step-with-road-to-study">International Trade and Business: First Step with Road to Study</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The application process can seem daunting, but with the right guidance, it&#8217;s actually much easier than you think. This is where Road to Study comes in.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-documents-and-process">Application Documents and Process</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The following documents are usually requested:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>High school diploma and transcript</li>



<li>Passport photocopy</li>



<li>English proficiency certificate (TOEFL, IELTS or the university&#8217;s own exam)</li>



<li>Letter of intent</li>



<li>Letters of recommendation (not mandatory but recommended)</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">All applications are submitted online and the acceptance process usually takes 2-4 weeks.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="why-you-should-apply-with-road-to-study">Why You Should Apply with Road to Study</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">I made a lot of mistakes when I applied on my own. I uploaded documents in the wrong format, missed deadlines, wore the wrong outfit to the visa interview. Road to Study plans the process for you, checks the documents and maintains contact with the university. You can also find all the latest information about the university on <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">roadtostudy.com</a>.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="common-mistakes-and-advice">Common Mistakes and Advice</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The visa application process is an important step for foreign students wishing to study in Turkey. Students apply for a visa from the consulates by preparing the necessary documents together with the documents of the university they have been accepted to. Details of this process can be found at <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/ogrenci-vizesi-basvuru-sureci/"><strong>Visa Guide for International Students in Turkey</strong></a>.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-07-24T09:14:53Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-15T18:47:14Z', "featured_image" = '{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/international-trade-and-business-1.webp","alt":"Özyeğin University International Trade and Business Campus","title":"international-trade-and-business"}' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'international-trade-and-business';
