<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you want to study management information systems, it&#8217;s up to you not only to get accepted, but also to get a high percentage of scholarships. With <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">RoadtoStudy&#8217;s experienced consultants</a> you can manage the process more consciously and professionally.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-difference-of-mis-education-at-ozyegin-university">The Difference of MIS Education at Ozyegin University</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Management Information Systems program at Ozyegin University does not stop with theory. With its international academic staff, global student profile and internship opportunities abroad, it educates its students in a well-rounded way. For someone who wants to pursue a career in management information systems, this combination really makes a difference.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="international-cadre-and-global-perspective">International Cadre and Global Perspective</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Most of the academics in the program have studied and worked in different continents. This provides students with not only theory but also practical applications in the business world. In addition, thanks to the high percentage of foreign students admitted to the program, the classroom environment is transformed into a real global business simulation.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="english-education-4-years-and-faculty-details">English Education, 4 Years and Faculty Details</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The MIS program is taught entirely in English and lasts four years. The course is offered under Özyeğin University&#8217;s Faculty of Business Administration and the annual fee is set at USD 22,000. <a class="" href="https://www.ozyegin.edu.tr/pdfviewer/isletme-2023-2024.php?csrt=2152483774568276679" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Faculty brochure can be found here</a>.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="service-sector-oriented-curriculum">Service Sector Oriented Curriculum</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Starting in the second year, students begin to receive intensive information about the service sectors in which Özyeğin University is strong. Especially in areas such as hotel management, aviation, finance and logistics, courses supported by practical examples are given.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="course-structure-and-specialization-process">Course Structure and Specialization Process</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The YBS program is far from a classical memorization system. Course contents are planned in a way that allows students to specialize in different fields. Even entrepreneurship is built into the courses.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="fundamentals-in-2nd-grade-specialties-in-3rd-grade">Fundamentals in 2nd Grade, Specialties in 3rd Grade</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">While the second year is mostly devoted to basic business and IT courses, in the third year students begin to identify their own areas of specialization through elective courses. During this period, they are encouraged to develop new business ideas and think entrepreneurially. Lessons are not only in the classroom; they are supported by company visits, case studies and guest speakers.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="4th-grade-capstone-project-and-sectoral-deepening">4th Grade Capstone Project and Sectoral Deepening</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The final year is spent with students doing an applied project in the sector of their choice and preparing a graduation thesis. In this way, they graduate with not only theoretical but also sectoral knowledge.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="applied-education-and-internship-opportunities">Applied Education and Internship Opportunities</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can&#8217;t become an MIS graduate just by studying; there is also the application of this job. Özyeğin University has established a truly exemplary system in this regard.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="8-week-compulsory-internship-real-experience">8-Week Compulsory Internship: Real Experience</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In many business schools in Turkey, internships are not compulsory. But things are different here. There is a compulsory 8-week internship in the YBS program and this internship is designed for students to get to know the sector, get used to office life and meet the business world before graduation.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="bilisim-competitions-and-shadowing-activities">Bilisim Competitions and Shadowing Activities</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Students are supported to participate in international information systems project competitions. They also have the chance to participate in experience programs called &#8220;shadowing&#8221; at major technology companies in Turkey and abroad. Thanks to these programs, students can observe the work life of a professional for one day. This provides a clear answer to the question &#8220;can I do this job?&#8221;</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="after-graduation-career-and-international-network">After Graduation: Career and International Network</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Careers for YBS graduates are not limited to Turkey. One of the program&#8217;s greatest strengths is that it offers students a global network.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="fields-and-companies-where-graduates-work">Fields and Companies Where Graduates Work</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Graduates can pursue careers in data analytics, systems management, ERP consultancy, business intelligence, project management and many other fields. They can work in both local and multinational companies. Among them are those working in companies such as Deloitte, PwC and IBM.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="overseas-education-internship-and-cooperation-opportunities">Overseas Education, Internship and Cooperation Opportunities</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Özyeğin University attaches great importance to Erasmus and global exchange programs. Students can go to various cities in Europe or America for both education and internship. This means the opportunity to gain global experience before graduation. In addition, thanks to the institutions that the university partners with, students start with an advantage in finding a job abroad after graduation.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


