<iframe loading="lazy" title="Bir Bölüm Üç Açı - Psikoloji Mezun &amp; Öğrenci" width="720" height="405" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Z_49RT5lTMc?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
</div></figure>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Studying psychology is a passion for many people. Understanding behavior, delving into the inner world of people, and sometimes even shedding light on our own lives&#8230; Özyeğin University Psychology Department offers a modern and research-oriented environment for students who want to embark on this journey.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="psychology-department-at-the-faculty-of-social-sciences">Psychology Department at the Faculty of Social Sciences</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Department of Psychology is part of Ozyegin University&#8217;s Faculty of Social Sciences. The language of instruction is entirely in English. This provides a great advantage especially for students from abroad. Courses are supported by both theoretical and applied content. Laboratories for fields such as experimental psychology, neuropsychology and clinical psychology are actively used.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="academic-staff-and-educational-approach">Academic Staff and Educational Approach</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The faculty members in the department are experienced academics who are involved in national and international projects. The education system is not just about listening to lectures and taking exams. Students participate in research, take part in consultancy projects and some even work on publishable papers. This practice-oriented approach gives students a strong start to their careers.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="psychology-department-fees-and-scholarship-opportunities">Psychology Department Fees and Scholarship Opportunities</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Özyeğin University offers detailed and flexible payment plans in this regard.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="fees-for-international-students-for-2025-2026">Fees for International Students for 2025-2026</h3>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<tr>
<th>Annual Tuition</th>
<th>Prepayment</th>
<th>Installment for Fall</th>
<th>Installment for Spring</th>
<th>Total</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>$22,000</td>
<td>$1,000</td>
<td>$10,000</td>
<td>$11,000</td>
<td>$22,000</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>
<blockquote class="wp-block-quote">


<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Note:</strong> The fee for the English Preparatory Program is the same as the psychology undergraduate program. The fee does not include health insurance, use of technology, dormitory and meal fees.</p>


</blockquote>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-the-50-scholarship-payment-plan-works">How the 50% Scholarship Payment Plan Works</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you receive a 50% scholarship at the time of application, your annual tuition fee drops to $11,000. In this case, the payment plan is as follows:</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Down Payment:</strong> $1,000</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Installment (Fall Semester):</strong> $4,500 (after deducting the down payment)</li>



<li><strong>Installment (Spring Semester):</strong> $5,500</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The university also offers sample payment plans for different scholarship rates such as 45%, 40% and 35%. You can find detailed information about these scholarships, which vary according to achievement and application time, on the <strong><a href="https://roadtostudy.com/ozyegin-universitesi-egitim-ucretleri/" data-type="post" data-id="3013">Özyeğin University Tuition Fees and Payment Options</a></strong> page.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="other-scholarship-options-and-application-criteria">Other Scholarship Options and Application Criteria</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">During the application evaluation process, faculty members may award <strong>academic merit-based entrance scholarships</strong> based on academic background and application documents. These scholarships are automatically evaluated and do not require any additional application. You&#8217;ll find out if you&#8217;ve won a scholarship in your <strong>acceptance email</strong>.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For more detailed and up-to-date information, please visit <a href="https://studentservices.ozyegin.edu.tr/tr/burs-ve-finansal-destek" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Özyeğin University Scholarship Terms and Conditions page</a>.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="english-psychology-department-ozyegin-difference">English Psychology Department: Ozyegin Difference</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Studying in English can sometimes feel intimidating, especially if you are just starting university life. But at Özyeğin University, this process is well structured. It doesn&#8217;t just give you a language; it also prepares you for an international psychology literature.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="education-language-and-program-content">Education Language and Program Content</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">All courses are taught in English. In addition to basic courses such as developmental psychology, cognitive psychology, social psychology, students are offered the chance to deepen their interests with elective courses. In addition, students can minor or double major if they wish.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-preparatory-class-and-the-compulsory-education-process">The Preparatory Class and the Compulsory Education Process</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you do not have language proficiency, you need to take a one-year preparatory education. &#8220;English Preparatory Education&#8221; costs the same as the undergraduate program. During the preparatory year, you develop your academic language skills and adapt to the university. Afterwards, you transfer to the undergraduate program and your specialization process starts for 4 years.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="campus-life-and-student-experience-in-istanbul">Campus Life and Student Experience in Istanbul</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Özyeğin University stands out not only for its academic success but also for the campus life it offers. The university is located in a lush green area in Çekmeköy district of Istanbul, and I think this in itself is a reason for preference.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="campus-facilities-and-social-life">Campus Facilities and Social Life</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The campus has gyms, libraries, research laboratories and open spaces. The experimental laboratories, especially for psychology students, are really impressive. In addition, academic life is well balanced with social life thanks to the societies and student clubs that are active at the school.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Founded by psychology students at Ozyegin University, <strong>PsychOZ</strong> is an active student club that aims to strengthen solidarity within the department and support professional development. Since 2014, it has been organizing events that reach not only students within the university but also many psychology enthusiasts from Turkey and abroad. </p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="dormitories-transportation-and-living-expenses">Dormitories, Transportation and Living Expenses</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The university&#8217;s own dormitories are located on campus. Dormitories are generally comfortable, but options vary depending on budget. Meal fees are average for on-campus. Although Istanbul is an expensive city in general, the location of the campus can be considered a little more affordable.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In terms of transportation, you use the Istanbul Card system. Metro, bus and minibus connections keep you connected to the city. You are not isolated from the city, but you are far from its chaos.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are curious about the other faculties and departments offered by Özyeğin University, you can check out our article <strong><a href="https://roadtostudy.com/ozyegin-universitesi-fakulteleri/" data-type="post" data-id="3027">Meet the Faculties and Departments of Özyeğin University</a></strong>.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-happens-when-you-graduate-careers-in-psychology">What Happens When You Graduate? Careers in Psychology</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="work-opportunities-in-turkey-and-abroad">Work Opportunities in Turkey and Abroad</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">After graduation, students can pursue many different fields: clinical psychology, human resources, educational counseling, neuropsychology, research centers&#8230; Some even go directly to graduate school abroad. Özyeğin University&#8217;s international collaborations and Erasmus opportunities also facilitate these transitions.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="internship-opportunities-and-counseling-support">Internship Opportunities and Counseling Support</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Internship is an important part of the program. Especially in the 3rd and 4th year, students can do internships at hospitals, private counseling centers or educational institutions in Istanbul. The individual counseling and CV workshops offered by the Career Center also provide good support. In other words, the university does not just graduate you, it prepares you for business life.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="build-your-future-at-ozyegin-university">Build Your Future at Ozyegin University!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Özyeğin University offers you a strong ground for both scientific depth and personal development. It makes a difference with its campus, academic staff and scholarship systems.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">But most importantly, being a student here is not just about getting a diploma; it&#8217;s about getting to know yourself, developing yourself and maybe even helping others. If you are ready to take the first step on this path, now is the time to apply.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-07-24T09:58:47Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-15T18:47:11Z', "featured_image" = '{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/ozyegin-universitesi-psychology.webp","alt":"Ozyegin University Psychology Club","title":"ozyegin-universitesi-psychology"}' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'ozyegin-university-psychology-department';
