udy in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/visa-and-residence-fees-in-turkey.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/visa-and-residence-fees-in-turkey.webp","width":"1168","height":"880","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/visa-and-residence-fees-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/visa-and-residence-fees-in-turkey/","name":"Visa and Residence Fees in Turkey: Costs &amp; Payment Methods","datePublished":"2025-12-13T16:46:13+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:48:47+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/visa-and-residence-fees-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Visa and Residence Fees in Turkey: Costs &amp; Payment Methods","keywords":"Visa and Residence Fees","datePublished":"2025-12-13T16:46:13+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:48:47+03:00","articleSection":"Visa and Immigration","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Visa and residence fees are&nbsp;basically&nbsp;mandatory fees that must be paid for the application. However, you should keep in mind that often additional","name":"Visa and Residence Fees in Turkey: Costs &amp; Payment Methods","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/visa-and-residence-fees-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/visa-and-residence-fees-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/visa-and-residence-fees-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/visa-and-residence-fees-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Turkey is a country that attracts international students, especially with its educational opportunities, culture and history.</strong></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">However, there are many visa and residence permit options that those who want to travel to Turkey or live there long-term must face. In this blog post, we will cover the costs, payment methods and most common questions about visas and residence permits in Turkey. If you are thinking how complicated these processes are, you are not alone. Get ready for a journey full of answers and suggestions!</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="visa-and-residence-fees-in-turkey">Visa and Residence Fees in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are many categories of visas available to those wishing to travel to Turkey. Within the major categories of entry visas, residence permits and national visas, each has its own costs and conditions.&nbsp;<em>entry visas, just as their name suggests, are issued to be used for one or multiple entries into Turkey, while residence permits are generally for those who plan to stay in Turkey for an extended period of time.</em>&nbsp;There are also national visas, which are issued for specific purposes such as study, work or family reunification.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">This diversity can cause a complicated process for&nbsp;<strong>international students</strong>&nbsp;applying for a visa. Therefore, it is important to have a good understanding of the type of visa and the point of application. For example, a single entry visa costs&nbsp;<strong>137 USD</strong>, while a multiple entry visa often costs more.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="visa-types-and-pricing">Visa Types and Pricing</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Visa types in Turkey can be divided into two main categories:&nbsp;<strong>short-term (tourist, business)</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>long-term (student, work)</strong>. Short-term visas are usually valid for up to 90 days and visa fees may vary depending on the country of application. Long-term visas are required for stays of more than 90 days and each has its own fees and processing times.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Visa fees are an official fee that must be paid to apply for a visa in Turkey. Service fees are fees charged for additional services and will appear when you make transactions in places known as application centers.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="turkey-visa-fees-2025">Turkey Visa Fees (2025)</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Current visa fees for 2025 vary depending on the legal regulations in Turkey. For example, a single entry visa costs&nbsp;<strong>137 USD</strong>, while a multiple entry visa usually costs more. If you want to get a Schengen visa, there are different prices, such as&nbsp;<strong>90 Euros</strong>&nbsp;for adults and&nbsp;<strong>45 Euros</strong>&nbsp;for children aged 6-12.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Visa fees for other countries vary in a similar way. For example, visa fees for&nbsp;<strong>Hungary or France</strong>&nbsp;in European countries usually range between&nbsp;<strong>110-120 Euros</strong>. However, it is important to be aware that these fees will be two separate costs, both the application center and the visa fee.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="single-entry-and-multiple-entry-visas">Single Entry and Multiple Entry Visas</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">As the name suggests, a single entry visa allows you to enter Turkey only once. If your trip is limited to one time only, this type of visa will be sufficient. However, if you get a multiple entry visa, you can enter Turkey more than once. The fees for this visa type vary for citizens of different countries.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Because the visa application process differs depending on the type of application, we recommend a lengthy preparation to get the&nbsp;<strong>right documents and pay the fees</strong>. Choosing the right type of visa is vital when considering the most suitable option for students considering a long-term stay.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="residence-permit-fees">Residence Permit Fees</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Foreign nationals planning to stay in Turkey for more than 90 days are required to obtain a residence permit. Types of residence permits include short-term, family, student and work permits. Each permit has different fees and costs depending on the type. For example, applying for a&nbsp;<strong>student residence permit</strong>&nbsp;can result in fees that typically range from&nbsp;<strong>50-100 USD</strong>.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are planning to stay in Turkey for a longer period of time, keep in mind that these fees are updated every year and it is worth checking the official page of the Ministry of Interior. For more information on current tariffs and application processes, it is useful to visit the website of&nbsp;<a href="https://www.goc.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">General Directorate of Migration Management</a>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="short-term-and-long-term-residence-permits">Short Term and Long Term Residence Permits</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Short-term residence permits are for those planning to stay for up to&nbsp;<strong>90 days</strong>&nbsp;and generally offer a simpler and faster application process. Long-term residence permits for purposes such as study, work or family reunification are subject to a more complex process. In many cases, short-term permits can be obtained in combination with a tourist visa.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Long-term residence permits usually require more documentation and background checks. During your studies, it is important to make a&nbsp;<strong>good plan</strong>&nbsp;to collect the necessary documents and pay the fees on time. Both types of residence permits may vary depending on specific rules and regulations, so you should prepare all your documents meticulously before submitting your applications.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="scope-of-wages-and-additional-expenses">Scope of Wages and Additional Expenses</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Visa and residence fees are&nbsp;<strong>basically</strong>&nbsp;mandatory fees that must be paid for the application. However, you should keep in mind that often additional services will also have a cost. Service fees are charged for additional services such as document submission at the application center, biometrics, etc. and these costs are added to the visa fee. In fact, you have to pay a fee for the provision of these services.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Not only the visa application fee, but also additional costs such as&nbsp;<strong>travel health insurance</strong>, document translations, notarizations, etc. must be taken into account. Therefore, when creating your planned budget, it is important to think about the total cost and take these expenses into account. Make sure you allow enough time to prepare your&nbsp;<strong>relevant documents and services</strong>&nbsp;to avoid additional costs.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="payment-methods">Payment Methods</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Payment of visa and residence fees may vary depending on the type of visa you are applying for and where you are applying. Applications submitted through application centers or consulates usually accept payment in&nbsp;<strong>cash (in dollars)</strong>&nbsp;or by debit card. However, some application centers only accept cash. It is therefore worth contacting the relevant center before you go&nbsp;<em>to check what payment options are available</em>.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">E-visa applications or online residence permit extensions allow online payment by credit/debit card. Official authorities, such as the&nbsp;<strong>Migration Authority</strong>&nbsp;or the&nbsp;<strong>Ministry of Foreign Affairs</strong>, may often ask you to go to a contracted bank branch or tax office for payments. For electronic payments, you can usually make your transactions in accordance with the instructions on the application page.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="visa-and-residency-fees-make-your-transactions-today">Visa and Residency Fees: Make Your Transactions Today!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are planning to travel to Turkey or live here for an extended period of time, you can speed up the visa and residence process with the right information and preparation. Turkey is a great destination for studying, exploring the culture or taking advantage of business opportunities. With <strong>good planning</strong>, you can minimize your financial losses and make the application process easier. Immediately <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/en/student-visa-preparations-checklist/" data-type="link" data-id="https://roadtostudy.com/en/student-visa-preparations-checklist/">Visa Preparations Before Coming to Turkey: Checklist</a> and complete your deficiencies!</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How much does a Turkish visa cost and who has to pay?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey visa fees vary depending on the type of visa and the country of application. There is a visa exemption for citizens of some countries.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="is-visa-service-fee-and-visa-fee-the-same-thing">Is visa service fee and visa fee the same thing?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">No, the visa fee is a mandatory government fee, while the service fee is charged for additional services provided by the application center.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-to-apply-for-an-e-visa">How to apply for an E-visa</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">E-visa applications are submitted online through the official e-visa portal. To complete your application, you must pay by credit card with the required documents.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-to-pay-the-residence-permit-fee">How to pay the residence permit fee</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Residence permit fees can usually be paid through contracted banks or tax offices. The official website of the Migration Management provides up-to-date information.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="if-my-visa-application-is-rejected-can-i-get-a-refund-of-the-fee-i-paid">If my visa application is rejected, can I get a refund of the fee I paid?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Visa fees and service charges are charged for processing the application and are non-refundable in the event of refusal.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-12-13T13:46:13Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-15T18:48:47Z', "featured_image" = '{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/visa-and-residence-fees-in-turkey.webp","alt":"Visa and Residence Fees in Turkey: Costs and Payment Methods","title":"visa-and-residence-fees-in-turkey"}' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'visa-and-residence-fees-in-turkey';
