":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-cocuk-sahibi-ogrenciler-vize-izni/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-cocuk-sahibi-ogrenciler-vize-izni/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/what-is-a-family-residence-permit-in-turkey-1024x772-1.webp"},"inLanguage":"tr","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-cocuk-sahibi-ogrenciler-vize-izni/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p><span style="font-size: inherit; font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, BlinkMacSystemFont, ''Segoe UI'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, ''Apple Color Emoji'', ''Segoe UI Emoji'', ''Segoe UI Symbol'';">Türkiye’de eğitim görmek, özellikle çocuk sahibi öğrenciler için birçok fırsat ve zorluğu beraberinde getiriyor. Eğitim kalitesi ve kültürel zenginliklerin sunulduğu Türkiye, çocuk sahibi öğrenciler için güvenli bir ortam sağlamak amacıyla çeşitli yasal süreçler ve haklar belirlemiştir. Bu yazımızda, Türkiye’de eğitim gören çocuk sahibi öğrencilerin vize ve ikamet izinleri ile ilgili süreçleri ayrıntılı olarak ele alacağız.</span></p>
<h2 id="h-ogrenci-vizesi-nedir-ve-kimler-alabilir" class="wp-block-heading">Öğrenci Vizesi Nedir ve Kimler Alabilir?</h2>
<p>Türkiye’de bir eğitim kurumunda okumak isteyen yabancı öğrencilerin, Türkiye’ye girişte “öğrenci vizesi” almaları zorunludur. Bu vize, <a style="color: #00c2ff !important;" href="https://www.konsolosluk.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">başvurulan Türk Konsolosluğu’ndan</a> alınmakta ve genellikle öğrencinin kabul edildiği okuldan aldığı kabul mektubuna dayanılarak verilmektedir. Vize süresi, öğrencinin eğitim süresine bağlı olarak değişiklik gösterir ama genelde ilk girişte 90 gün ile sınırlıdır. Bu süreçte öğrencinin, Türkiye’de kalabilmesi için kesinlikle “öğrenci ikamet izni” almak zorunda olduğunu unutmamak gerekir.</p>
<p>Öğrenci vizesinin alınabilmesi için, bazı şartlara uyulması gerekmektedir. Bu şartlardan bazıları:</p>
<ul>
<li>Yeterli mali kaynaklara sahip olmak,</li>
<li>Doğru belgelerle başvuru yapmak,</li>
<li>Türkiye&#8217;ye girişi düzenleyen diğer hukuki prosedürleri takip etmek.</li>
</ul>
<p>Özellikle, vize sürecinin her aşamasında dikkatli olunmalı ve gerekli belgelerin eksiksiz olması sağlanmalıdır.</p>
<h2 id="h-cocuk-sahibi-öğenciler-icin-ozel-durumlar" class="wp-block-heading">Çocuk Sahibi Öğrenciler için Özel Durumlar</h2>
<p>Çocuk sahibi olan ve Türkiye&#8217;de eğitim gören öğrenciler için, çocukları da Türkiye’de kalacaksa, vize ve ikamet izni başvurusu yapmak şarttır. Eğer çocuğun ebeveynlerinden biri başka bir ülkede yaşıyorsa, vize başvurusu sırasında diğer ebeveynden noter tasdikli muvafakatname talep edilecektir. Bu durum, çocuğun Türkiye’ye yasal ve güvenli bir şekilde gelmesini sağlamak için son derece önemlidir. Aksi takdirde, çocuğun vize süreci aksayabilir veya reddedilebilir.</p>
<p>Türkiye’de yasal olarak ikamet iznine sahip bir ebeveynin çocuğu, doğrudan “aile ikamet izni” kapsamında Türkiye’de kalma hakkına sahiptir. Aile ikamet izni, ebeveynin ikamet süresine ve başvuruda belirtilen koşullara dayanmaktadır. Bu nedenle, aile ikamet izninin alınması sürecinde, ebeveynin vize ve ikamet durumu dikkatlice değerlendirilmelidir.</p>
<h3 id="h-aile-ikamet-izni" class="wp-block-heading">Aile İkamet İzni</h3>
<p>Aile ikamet izni, yalnızca bir ebeveynin ikamet izniyle sınırlıdır ve çoğu zaman her başvuruda en fazla üç yıl süreyle verilir. Bu bağlamda, tüm çocuklar için ayrı ayrı ikamet izni almak mümkün olsa da, sadece bir eşin aile ikamet izni alabileceği unutulmamalıdır. Aile ikamet izniyle Türkiye&#8217;de bulunan çocuklar, 18 yaşına kadar ilk ve ortaöğretim kurumlarında öğrenci ikamet izni almadan eğitim görme hakkına sahiptir.</p>
<p>Aynı zamanda, aile ikamet izni için başvuru yapan yabancının destekleyicisi, yani ebeveynin bazı şartları yerine getirmesi gerekmektedir:</p>
<ul>
<li>En az bir yıldır Türkiye’de geçerli bir ikamet iznine sahip olmalı,</li>
<li>Tüm aile üyelerini kapsayan geçerli sağlık sigortası yaptırmış olmalıdır,</li>
<li>Her bir aile üyesi için asgari ücretin üçte biri kadar gelir elde ettiğini belgelemelidir.</li>
</ul>
<p>Bu şartlar, aile birliğinin korunmasını ve çocukların güvenli bir ortamda eğitim almasını sağlamak için oluşturulmuştur.</p>
<h3 id="h-destekleyici-sponsor-sartlari" class="wp-block-heading">Destekleyici (Sponsor) Şartları</h3>
<p>Aile ikamet izni için başvuru yapacak olan yabancının, belirli şartları ve yükümlülükleri bulunmaktadır:</p>
<ul>
<li>En az bir yıldır Türkiye’de geçerli bir ikamet iznine sahip olması gerekmektedir.</li>
<li>Adres kayıt sisteminde kaydı olmalı ve tüm aile üyeleri için geçerli sağlık sigortası yaptırmış olmalıdır.</li>
<li>Destekleyicinin, son 5 yıl içinde aile düzenine karşı herhangi bir suç işlememiş olması da önemli bir şarttır.</li>
</ul>
<p>Eğer aile ikamet izni sona ererse, yasal durumda bazı değişiklikler gerçekleşebilir. Örneğin, ebeveynin izni bitmişse veya aile birliği ortadan kalkmışsa, çocuk kısa dönem ikamet iznine başvurabilir. Bu noktada, yasal süreçlerin dikkatlice takip edilmesi ve gerekli belgelerin zamanında başvuruya eklenmesi oldukça önemlidir.</p>
<h2 id="h-basvuru-ve-muvafakat-islemleri" class="wp-block-heading">Başvuru ve Muvafakat İşlemleri</h2>
<p>18 yaş altındaki çocukların vize başvuruları sırasında, hem anne hem de babalarından muvafakatname alınması zorunludur. Bu, çocuğun yasal ve güvenli biçimde Türkiye’ye gelmesini sağlamaya yöneliktir. Özellikle tek başına veya yalnız bir ebeveynle Türkiye’ye gelen çocuklarda, bu belgelerin tamamlanması konusunda ciddiyetle yaklaşılmalıdır.</p>
<p>Yalnızca muvafakatname yeterli olmayabilir; velayetin de belgelenmesi gerekmektedir. Bu noktada, hukuki süreçlerin takip edilmesi önemlidir. Herkes için geçerli olan bu şartlar, çocuğun güvenliğini sağlamak ve yasaların getirdiği sorumlulukları yerine getirmek açısından kritik önem taşır.</p>
<h2 id="h-cocuklarin-egitim-haklari" class="wp-block-heading">Çocukların Eğitim Hakları</h2>
<p>Türkiye&#8217;de aile ikamet izni ile yaşayan çocuklar, ilköğretim ve ortaöğretim kurumlarında 18 yaşına kadar eğitim alma hakkına sahiptir. Bu durumda, çocukların ayrıca öğrenci ikamet izni almalarına gerek bulunmamaktadır. Bu, ailelerin çocuklarının Türkiye&#8217;deki eğitimlerini sürdürebilmeleri açısından büyük bir avantaj sağlamaktadır.</p>
<p>Ancak 18 yaşını dolduran veya lise sonrası üniversite eğitimi almak isteyen öğrenciler, ayrı bir öğrenci ikamet izni başvurusunda bulunmak zorundadır. Bu nedenle, ailelerin çocuklarının eğitim planlamalarını yaparken, bu geçiş sürecinin gerekliliklerini dikkate almaları önemlidir.</p>
<h2>Sıkça Sorulan Sorular</h2>
<h3 data-start="272" data-end="325">Türkiye’de öğrenci ikamet izni kimlere verilir?</h3>
<p data-start="326" data-end="627">Türkiye’de öğrenci ikamet izni, Türkiye’de eğitim almaya hak kazanan yabancı öğrencilere verilir. Kabul mektubu, kayıt belgesi veya öğrenci belgesi bu başvurunun temelini oluşturur. Ayrıca Türkiye’de yasal olarak ikamet eden bir yabancının çocuğu da uygun şartları sağlıyorsa bu haktan yararlanabilir.</p>
<h3 data-start="629" data-end="689">Aile ikamet izni ile Türkiye’de eğitim görülebilir mi?</h3>
<p data-start="690" data-end="940">Aile ikamet izniyle Türkiye’ye gelen çocuklar, 18 yaşına kadar ilk ve ortaöğretim kurumlarında eğitim görebilir. Ancak yükseköğrenim için bu izin yeterli değildir; üniversiteye geçiş aşamasında mutlaka öğrenci ikamet izni başvurusu yapılması gerekir.</p>
<h3 data-start="942" data-end="976">Muvafakatname neden istenir?</h3>
<p data-start="977" data-end="1242">18 yaş altındaki yabancı çocukların tek ebeveynle ya da yalnız seyahat ettiği durumlarda, diğer ebeveynden alınmış muvafakatname zorunlu tutulur. Bu belge, olası hukuki riskleri önlemek ve çocuğun güvenliğini resmî olarak garanti altına almak amacıyla talep edilir.</p>
<h3 data-start="1244" data-end="1295">Türkiye’de kalış süresi dolarsa ne yapılmalı?</h3>
<p data-start="1296" data-end="1568">Aile ya da öğrenci ikamet izni süresi dolmadan önce, mevcut izni yenilemek veya uygun olan yeni bir ikamet türüne başvurmak gerekir. Sürenin aşılması hem para cezası hem de ülkeye giriş kısıtlamalarına yol açabileceği için başvurunun zamanında yapılması kritik önem taşır.</p>
<h3 data-start="1570" data-end="1613">Aile ikamet izni sona ererse ne olur?</h3>
<p data-start="1614" data-end="1855">Aile ikamet izni geçerliliğini yitirirse örneğin ebeveynin izni bitmişse veya aile birliği ortadan kalkmışsa çocuk, şartları sağladığı takdirde kısa dönem ikamet iznine geçiş yapabilir. Böylece eğitim sürecinin kesintiye uğramaması sağlanır.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2025-06-18T14:19:41Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T19:24:20Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/what-is-a-family-residence-permit-in-turkey-1024x772-1.webp","alt":"Türkiye''de Çocuk Sahibi Öğrenciler İçin Vize ve İkamet İzni","title":"what-is-a-family-residence-permit-in-turkey-1024&#215;772"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'tr' AND "slug" = 'turkiye-cocuk-sahibi-ogrenciler-vize-izni' );
UPDATE "ec_posts" SET "source_seo" = '{"title":"Companion Visa for Spouses of Students in Turkey","description":"Turkey not only offers an academic opportunity for foreign students, but also allows them to have their families with them. If you are a student studying in","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Companion Visa for Spouses of Students in Turkey","ogDescription":"Turkey not only offers an academic opportunity for foreign students, but also allows them to have their families with them. If you are a student studying in","ogImage":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey.webp","twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Companion Visa for Spouses of Students in Turkey","twitterDescription":"Turkey not only offers an academic opportunity for foreign students, but also allows them to have their families with them. If you are a student studying in","canonicalPath":"/en/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiye-aile-ikamet-izni/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey.webp","width":"1168","height":"880","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey/","name":"Companion Visa for Spouses of Students in Turkey","datePublished":"2025-12-14T16:57:26+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:48:46+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Companion Visa for Spouses of Students in Turkey","keywords":"Companion Visa,Spouses","datePublished":"2025-12-14T16:57:26+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:48:46+03:00","articleSection":"Visa and Immigration","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Turkey not only offers an academic opportunity for foreign students, but also allows them to have their families with them. If you are a student studying in","name":"Companion Visa for Spouses of Students in Turkey","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey not only offers an academic opportunity for foreign students, but also allows them to have their families with them. If you are a student studying in Turkey and want to live with your spouse or children, you may have heard the term “family residence permit” instead of “companion visa”. In this process, the conditions and documents required for student families to come to Turkey and stay here legally are very important.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-is-a-family-residence-permit">What is a Family Residence Permit?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a href="https://roadtostudy.com/en/what-is-a-family-residence-permit-in-turkey/">Family residence permit</a> is a type of permit that gives the spouse and children of a foreign student studying in Turkey or a foreigner legally residing in Turkey the right to stay in Turkey legally for a certain period of time. Its purpose is to enable the family to live together and to protect the legal status of the family. This permit supports family members to be side by side in Turkey for a certain period of time and aims to preserve family unity. For more information, please visit <a href="https://www.goc.gov.tr/ikamet-izni-cesitleri" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">The official page of the Migration Authority</a>. It is quite common for foreign students, especially those studying in Turkey, to want to live with their families. The family residence permit is valid for the duration of the student’s studies, during which time spouses and children can live in Turkey. Moreover, with this kind of leave, family members feel the support and solidarity that comes with being a family.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-requirements-and-documents">Application Requirements and Documents</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In order to obtain a family residence permit, the spouse and children of a foreigner with a student residence permit in Turkey must provide documentation that they meet certain requirements. Firstly, the sponsor (i.e. the student or legal resident) must have been a legal resident in Turkey for at least 1 year. He/she must also have a valid health insurance that covers all family members. In other words, it is very important for each individual to have <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/en/student-health-insurance-in-turkey/" data-type="link" data-id="https://roadtostudy.com/en/student-health-insurance-in-turkey/">health insurance</a> in order to maintain a healthy family life. The list of documents required for the application also includes certain standards. These documents include the application petition, Residence Declaration Form, 4 passport size photos, passport and the identity card of the spouse in Turkey. You will also need to prove the existence of your family with a marriage certificate or similar official documents. The complete and accurate preparation of these documents is critical for the application process to proceed without a hitch.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-process">Application Process</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When applying for a family residence permit, the first step to take is to enter Turkey with a valid visa if you come from a country that is subject to a visa. There are countries where you can enter Turkey without a visa, in such cases you can enter directly. However, it is useful to review the visa requirements. In short, after entering Turkey with a visa, the most important thing to do is to apply to the Provincial Migration Administration within 30 days. You must submit the necessary documents in this process. Once your application for a residence permit has been submitted, the process of evaluation of the application begins. The duration of the family residence permit cannot exceed the duration of the residence permit of the supporting student. It is usually granted for initial applications for up to 3 years. Depending on the status of your marriage and the legal status of the sponsor, this period can be extended. So, if you and your family are planning to live in Turkey for a long period of time, it would be useful to have some information on how this process works.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="rights-recognized-with-family-residence-permit">Rights Recognized with Family Residence Permit</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The family residence permit provides foreigners with various rights in addition to the right to reside legally in Turkey. These rights are specifically regulated under the&nbsp;<a href="https://www5.tbmm.gov.tr/tutanaklar/KANUNLAR_KARARLAR/kanuntbmmc097/kanuntbmmc097/kanuntbmmc09706458.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Law No. 6458 on Foreigners and International Protection</a></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="right-to-education">Right to Education</h4>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Family residence permit holders <strong>foreign children</strong> under the age of 18 have the right to receive education in primary and secondary education institutions (<strong>public schools</strong>) in Turkey on <strong>equal terms</strong> with Turkish citizens for the duration of their residence permit.</li>



<li>These children do not need to obtain a <strong>student residence permit</strong>.</li>



<li>Students over the age of 18 must apply for a <strong>student residence permit</strong> to study at higher education institutions (university).</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Health Services</strong></h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It is a condition that the sponsor has&nbsp;<strong>valid health insurance</strong></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">for all family members. This insurance allows you to benefit from health services in Turkey.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="legal-right-to-residence-and-travel">Legal Right to Residence and Travel</h4>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Family residence permit allows the foreigner to reside legally in Turkey.</li>



<li>Foreigners with a valid residence permit are <strong>visa exempt</strong> upon entry to Turkey.</li>



<li><strong>With the application certificate issued during the application evaluation phase</strong>, the foreigner may travel abroad for <strong>no more than 15 days</strong> in one departure.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="difference-with-student-residence-permit">Difference with Student Residence Permit</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Foreign students have their own residence permit to continue their studies in Turkey and this is called a “student residence permit”. This permit is valid only for the person who is studying. However, family members, i.e. spouses and children, must also apply for a family residence permit in order to live in Turkey. This difference requires a separate arrangement for the families of students studying in Turkey to be able to continue their lives here. If spouses and children will be studying at student institutions, they will also need to apply for their own special permits. A family residence permit is an important step for foreign students who want to live together as a family in Turkey.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="take-action-protect-your-family-integrity">Take Action: Protect Your Family Integrity!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Start taking the necessary steps to benefit from the educational opportunities Turkey offers and live here with your family now! The family residence permit will help you and your family to provide an important environment of support and solidarity. When you prepare your permits and documents meticulously, you can minimize the difficulties you will experience in this process. Take action now to gather the information you need and apply for the life in Turkey of your dreams!</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="1-is-a-companion-visa-the-same-as-a-family-residence-permit">1. Is a companion visa the same as a family residence permit?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">No. In practice in Turkey, the term “accompanying visa” is not commonly used; it is mainly applied for spouses and children under the “family residence permit”.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">2. Can someone who is in Turkey on a student visa bring their family?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yes, a foreigner with a student residence permit can apply for a family residence permit for his/her family to live in Turkey.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="3-is-it-possible-to-work-with-a-family-residence-permit">3. Is it possible to work with a family residence permit?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Spouses arriving with a family residence permit are only entitled to work in Turkey if they obtain a work permit. Otherwise, there is no automatic right to work.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="4-until-what-age-can-children-stay-with-a-family-residence-permit">4. Until what age can children stay with a family residence permit?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Children can stay and study in Turkey until the age of 18 with a family residence permit. Later in life, they can switch to a student residence permit if necessary.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-12-14T13:57:26Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-15T18:48:46Z', "featured_image" = '{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey.webp","alt":"Companion Visa for Spouses of Students in Turkey","title":"spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey"}' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey';
UPDATE "revisions" SET "data" = json_set("data", '$.source_seo', json('{"title":"Companion Visa for Spouses of Students in Turkey","description":"Turkey not only offers an academic opportunity for foreign students, but also allows them to have their families with them. If you are a student studying in","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Companion Visa for Spouses of Students in Turkey","ogDescription":"Turkey not only offers an academic opportunity for foreign students, but also allows them to have their families with them. If you are a student studying in","ogImage":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey.webp","twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Companion Visa for Spouses of Students in Turkey","twitterDescription":"Turkey not only offers an academic opportunity for foreign students, but also allows them to have their families with them. If you are a student studying in","canonicalPath":"/en/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiye-aile-ikamet-izni/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey.webp","width":"1168","height":"880","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey/","name":"Companion Visa for Spouses of Students in Turkey","datePublished":"2025-12-14T16:57:26+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:48:46+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Companion Visa for Spouses of Students in Turkey","keywords":"Companion Visa,Spouses","datePublished":"2025-12-14T16:57:26+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:48:46+03:00","articleSection":"Visa and Immigration","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Turkey not only offers an academic opportunity for foreign students, but also allows them to have their families with them. If you are a student studying in","name":"Companion Visa for Spouses of Students in Turkey","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/spouse-visa-for-students-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey not only offers an academic opportunity for foreign students, but also allows them to have their families with them. If you are a student studying in Turkey and want to live with your spouse or children, you may have heard the term “family residence permit” instead of “companion visa”. In this process, the conditions and documents required for student families to come to Turkey and stay here legally are very important.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-is-a-family-residence-permit">What is a Family Residence Permit?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a href="https://roadtostudy.com/en/what-is-a-family-residence-permit-in-turkey/">Family residence permit</a> is a type of permit that gives the spouse and children of a foreign student studying in Turkey or a foreigner legally residing in Turkey the right to stay in Turkey legally for a certain period of time. Its purpose is to enable the family to live together and to protect the legal status of the family. This permit supports family members to be side by side in Turkey for a certain period of time and aims to preserve family unity. For more information, please visit <a href="https://www.goc.gov.tr/ikamet-izni-cesitleri" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">The official page of the Migration Authority</a>. It is quite common for foreign students, especially those studying in Turkey, to want to live with their families. The family residence permit is valid for the duration of the student’s studies, during which time spouses and children can live in Turkey. Moreover, with this kind of leave, family members feel the support and solidarity that comes with being a family.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-requirements-and-documents">Application Requirements and Documents</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In order to obtain a family residence permit, the spouse and children of a foreigner with a student residence permit in Turkey must provide documentation that they meet certain requirements. Firstly, the sponsor (i.e. the student or legal resident) must have been a legal resident in Turkey for at least 1 year. He/she must also have a valid health insurance that covers all family members. In other words, it is very important for each individual to have <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/en/student-health-insurance-in-turkey/" data-type="link" data-id="https://roadtostudy.com/en/student-health-insurance-in-turkey/">health insurance</a> in order to maintain a healthy family life. The list of documents required for the application also includes certain standards. These documents include the application petition, Residence Declaration Form, 4 passport size photos, passport and the identity card of the spouse in Turkey. You will also need to prove the existence of your family with a marriage certificate or similar official documents. The complete and accurate preparation of these documents is critical for the application process to proceed without a hitch.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-process">Application Process</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When applying for a family residence permit, the first step to take is to enter Turkey with a valid visa if you come from a country that is subject to a visa. There are countries where you can enter Turkey without a visa, in such cases you can enter directly. However, it is useful to review the visa requirements. In short, after entering Turkey with a visa, the most important thing to do is to apply to the Provincial Migration Administration within 30 days. You must submit the necessary documents in this process. Once your application for a residence permit has been submitted, the process of evaluation of the application begins. The duration of the family residence permit cannot exceed the duration of the residence permit of the supporting student. It is usually granted for initial applications for up to 3 years. Depending on the status of your marriage and the legal status of the sponsor, this period can be extended. So, if you and your family are planning to live in Turkey for a long period of time, it would be useful to have some information on how this process works.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="rights-recognized-with-family-residence-permit">Rights Recognized with Family Residence Permit</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The family residence permit provides foreigners with various rights in addition to the right to reside legally in Turkey. These rights are specifically regulated under the&nbsp;<a href="https://www5.tbmm.gov.tr/tutanaklar/KANUNLAR_KARARLAR/kanuntbmmc097/kanuntbmmc097/kanuntbmmc09706458.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Law No. 6458 on Foreigners and International Protection</a></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="right-to-education">Right to Education</h4>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Family residence permit holders <strong>foreign children</strong> under the age of 18 have the right to receive education in primary and secondary education institutions (<strong>public schools</strong>) in Turkey on <strong>equal terms</strong> with Turkish citizens for the duration of their residence permit.</li>



<li>These children do not need to obtain a <strong>student residence permit</strong>.</li>



<li>Students over the age of 18 must apply for a <strong>student residence permit</strong> to study at higher education institutions (university).</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Health Services</strong></h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It is a condition that the sponsor has&nbsp;<strong>valid health insurance</strong></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">for all family members. This insurance allows you to benefit from health services in Turkey.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="legal-right-to-residence-and-travel">Legal Right to Residence and Travel</h4>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Family residence permit allows the foreigner to reside legally in Turkey.</li>



<li>Foreigners with a valid residence permit are <strong>visa exempt</strong> upon entry to Turkey.</li>



<li><strong>With the application certificate issued during the application evaluation phase</strong>, the foreigner may travel abroad for <strong>no more than 15 days</strong> in one departure.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="difference-with-student-residence-permit">Difference with Student Residence Permit</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Foreign students have their own residence permit to continue their studies in Turkey and this is called a “student residence permit”. This permit is valid only for the person who is studying. However, family members, i.e. spouses and children, must also apply for a family residence permit in order to live in Turkey. This difference requires a separate arrangement for the families of students studying in Turkey to be able to continue their lives here. If spouses and children will be studying at student institutions, they will also need to apply for their own special permits. A family residence permit is an important step for foreign students who want to live together as a family in Turkey.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="take-action-protect-your-family-integrity">Take Action: Protect Your Family Integrity!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Start taking the necessary steps to benefit from the educational opportunities Turkey offers and live here with your family now! The family residence permit will help you and your family to provide an important environment of support and solidarity. When you prepare your permits and documents meticulously, you can minimize the difficulties you will experience in this process. Take action now to gather the information you need and apply for the life in Turkey of your dreams!</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="1-is-a-companion-visa-the-same-as-a-family-residence-permit">1. Is a companion visa the same as a family residence permit?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">No. In practice in Turkey, the term “accompanying visa” is not commonly used; it is mainly applied for spouses and children under the “family residence permit”.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">2. Can someone who is in Turkey on a student visa bring their family?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yes, a foreigner with a student residence permit can apply for a family residence permit for his/her family to live in Turkey.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="3-is-it-possible-to-work-with-a-family-residence-permit">3. Is it possible to work with a family residence permit?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Spouses arriving with a family residence permit are only entitled to work in Turkey if they obtain a work permit. Otherwise, there is no automatic right to work.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="4-until-what-age-can-children-stay-with-a-family-residence-permit">4. Until what age can children stay with a family residence permit?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Children can stay and study in Turkey until the age of 18 with a family residence permit. Later in life, they can switch to a student residence permit if necessary.</p>



