<div class="wp-block-paragraph">Another issue that should be paid particular attention in residence permit applications is the complete and accurate preparation of the documents. There are different types of residence permits, such as student residence permits and family residence permits, each with different requirements. By 2025, biometric data collection and e-residency card applications will also be rolled out to speed up processing times, so it is worthwhile to stay up to date and prepare your documents on time.</div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="travelvisa-status-with-the-eu-schengen-and-other-countries">Travel/Visa Status with the EU (Schengen) and Other Countries</h2>


<div class="wp-block-paragraph">Green (private) and gray (service) passport holders in Turkey may experience some confusion due to the European Union&#8217;s new ETIAS (Electronic Travel Authorization System). However, according to the government, the ETIAS system, which will be implemented in 2025, will not apply to Turkey. This means that green and gray passport holders will not need to apply for a new pre-visa to enter European countries. This is clearly stated in Turkey&#8217;s official sources, so the situation for holders of this type of passport is quite comfortable. On the other hand, the current Schengen visa requirement for standard passport (burgundy) holders to enter EU countries remains in place. This means that those planning to travel abroad from Turkey, especially for tourism and education purposes, will need to carefully prepare documents such as health insurance, a current passport, financial status and booking documents when applying for a visa.</div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-situation-for-green-and-gray-passport-holders">The Situation for Green and Gray Passport Holders</h3>


<div class="wp-block-paragraph"> For green and gray passport holders, Turkey&#8217;s advantages are quite evident. Thanks to all visa exemptions, holders of these passport types can travel with fewer documents, which is especially convenient for visiting family members and business travelers. However, it is important to keep up to date when you have travel plans. </div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="standard-passport-and-schengen-visa">Standard Passport and Schengen Visa</h3>


<div class="wp-block-paragraph">Standard passport holders must obtain a Schengen visa when traveling from Turkey to Europe. In this process, the health insurance requirement, which has been valid for years, is one of the most critical documents.</div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="touristic-commercial-and-transit-visas">Touristic, Commercial and Transit Visas</h2>


<div class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkey, tourist, commercial and transit visas are limited to a total of 90 days within 180 days. This is a factor that should be taken into consideration especially for students pursuing their education abroad. It is of utmost importance for international students to submit the necessary documents in full. The e-visa system is also a very practical way to enter Turkey. While the documents required for entry vary depending on the type, it is worth noting that using the e-visa system does not aggravate the existing visa conditions. When <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-visa-applications-errors/">Applying for a visa</a>, you should carefully prepare your documents and check up-to-date information.</div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="documents-required-to-enter-turkey">Documents Required to Enter Turkey</h3>


<div class="wp-block-paragraph">Documents required to enter Turkey include travel health insurance, up-to-date passport and reservation documents. When organizing your travel plans, it is very important to prepare these documents in full so that the entry process goes quickly and smoothly. You should also check your documents on time and carefully to avoid any problems on your trip.</div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="e-visa-system-and-conveniences">E-Visa System and Conveniences</h3>


<div class="wp-block-paragraph">The method of obtaining an e-visa provides a great convenience for citizens of many countries. Thanks to this system, you have the chance to make visa applications in a faster and more practical way. E-visa applications are made through online platforms and you can check the official <a style="color: #00c2ff !important;" href="https://www.mfa.gov.tr/yabancilarin-tabi-oldugu-vize-rejimi.tr.mfa" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Turkish Ministry of Foreign Affairs</a> website for up-to-date information and application processes for some passports.</div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="mandatory-travel-insurance-health-and-digitalization">Mandatory Travel Insurance, Health and Digitalization</h2>


<div class="wp-block-paragraph">In the post-COVID-19 period, one of the entry requirements to Turkey is a valid travel health insurance. This insurance is necessary for you to be able to benefit from health services during your trip. By 2025, this situation is set to become even stricter, which is why it is critical to have travel health insurance to cover you against potential health problems on your planned trip to Turkey. Digitalization plays a major role in the visa application and process. Online applications and appointment systems provide convenience for applicants and allow for faster visa processing. The fact that the control process of documents such as health insurance is carried out more strictly in the digital environment increases your travel safety.</div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="travel-health-insurance-obligation">Travel Health Insurance Obligation</h3>


<div class="wp-block-paragraph">Travel health insurance is mandatory upon entry to Turkey, which is vital for international students and visitors. This insurance protects you from high costs in terms of healthcare and provides a safe space in unexpected situations. Do not forget to take this insurance policy, which is valid for the duration of your trip.</div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="advantages-of-digital-application-and-appointment-system">Advantages of Digital Application and Appointment System</h3>


<div class="wp-block-paragraph">Online application and appointment systems speed up and facilitate all visa application processes. These systems allow you to keep track of your documents and manage the process better. Therefore, submitting your applications online will save you time and stress.</div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="dont-miss-education-opportunities-in-turkey">Don&#8217;t Miss Education Opportunities in Turkey!</h2>


<div class="wp-block-paragraph">Each step you take to study in Turkey is one of the most important parts of your educational journey. In light of all this information, start preparing your travel plan by reviewing visa and residence policies and gathering your necessary documents. Remember that with the right guidance and information, this process can be quite easy and fast. Take advantage of the best resources to take action and evaluate your opportunities to study in Turkey. For more information, check out our article &#8220;Turkey Student Visa: Application Process and Required Documents&#8221; for more information.</div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="can-the-visa-period-be-extended-for-entry-into-turkey">Can the visa period be extended for entry into Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Stay cannot be extended with a visa. For stays exceeding 90 days, a residence permit is required.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="is-health-insurance-mandatory-after-covid-19">Is health insurance mandatory after COVID-19?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yes. In the post-COVID-19 period, health insurance remains mandatory and is required for applications.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="is-a-pre-visa-required-to-enter-the-eu-with-a-greengrey-passport">Is a pre-visa required to enter the EU with a green/grey passport?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">No additional visa requirements. As of 2025, there are no additional pre-visa or ETIAS requirements in the EU for green and gray passport holders.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-are-the-sanctions-for-visa-or-residence-violations-in-turkey">What are the sanctions for visa or residence violations in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Administrative fines and/ or deportation may be imposed in case of violation of visa or residence permit duration.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="can-i-get-a-work-permit-with-a-student-visa">Can I get a work permit with a student visa?</h3>


<p>It may be possible to obtain a work permit in Turkey with a student visa under certain conditions. Find out your requirements for more information.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-02-25T07:44:58Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T18:39:03Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/visa-residence-policies-in-turkey-after-covid-19-1.webp","alt":"Visa and Residence Policies in Turkey after COVID-19","title":"visa-residence-policies-in-turkey-after-covid-19 (1)"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'visa-residence-policies-in-turkey-after-covid-19' );
